and a sense of danger,</i>

502
00:43:29,974 --> 00:43:36,471
<i>so they can strip us down to
something raw, animalistic, primal.</i>

503
00:43:39,317 --> 00:43:41,195
It's a sick game, and I
don't want to be a part of it.

504
00:43:41,219 --> 00:43:43,586
This isn't a game.
They'll kill us.

505
00:43:44,889 --> 00:43:49,554
But together, I know
we can find a way out.

506
00:43:50,128 --> 00:43:51,562
How can you be sure?

507
00:43:52,497 --> 00:43:58,903
There's a voice inside me,
telling me what I have to do.

508
00:43:59,337 --> 00:44:01,897
And it's telling me I need you.

509
00:44:21,492 --> 00:44:22,492
Shit.

510
00:44:38,042 --> 00:44:39,374
They have Logan.

511
00:44:43,314 --> 00:44:44,509
Help me.

512
00:44:45,283 --> 00:44:46,342
Help me.

513
00:44:49,620 --> 00:44:50,815
No.

514
00:44:55,626 --> 00:44:56,889
No more pretending.

515
00:45:08,306 --> 00:45:12,402
I thought you had no
appetite for war, boy.

516
00:45:12,710 --> 00:45:16,477
This is a declaration of war.

517
00:45:20,251 --> 00:45:21,719
El Lazo set us up.

518
00:45:21,986 --> 00:45:23,318
We can find him for you.

519
00:45:23,487 --> 00:45:26,582
You can find him for
us by joining him in hell.

520
00:45:30,595 --> 00:45:31,688
Dolores, run!

521
00:45:45,776 --> 00:45:46,903
Dolores?

522
00:46:00,625 --> 00:46:02,184
How did you do that?

523
00:46:02,860 --> 00:46:07,127
You said people come here to
change the story of their lives.

524
00:46:10,568 --> 00:46:13,732
I imagined a story where I
didn't have to be the damsel.

525
00:46:17,375 --> 00:46:20,607
Now that train is our only chance
of making it out of here alive.

526
00:46:53,811 --> 00:46:55,143
Motherfuckers.

527
00:47:08,759 --> 00:47:12,992
You pull that trigger, we'll
all go up in a ball of hellfire.

528
00:47:13,230 --> 00:47:15,392
So, why don't you
loosen your grip a mite?

529
00:47:23,441 --> 00:47:24,465
It's okay.

530
00:47:26,143 --> 00:47:27,270
I don't trust him.

531
00:47:27,445 --> 00:47:29,971
Which is the first step
to truly knowing me.

532
00:47:31,115 --> 00:47:32,743
Give me your gun, El Lazo.

533
00:47:38,656 --> 00:47:42,650
Now that we're all friends,
you can call me Lawrence.

534
00:47:43,661 --> 00:47:46,688
Now, why don't we settle
in. It's a long ride to the front.

535
00:47:58,342 --> 00:48:00,038
<i>You want a sip of this swill?</i>

536
00:48:04,448 --> 00:48:06,883
<i>Don't worry, it ain't nitro.</i>

537
00:48:15,326 --> 00:48:16,521
I'm coming.

538
00:48:37,248 --> 00:48:39,683
The girls are a little worn
out, but I can rouse one.

539
00:48:39,984 --> 00:48:41,384
You boys want some company?

540
00:48:41,552 --> 00:48:43,020
No. Just whiskey.

541
00:48:50,661 --> 00:48:53,859
Lawrence's donation
must be running low.

542
00:48:54,665 --> 00:48:56,600
But we're short on time.

543
00:48:56,867 --> 00:48:58,597
You need to buck up, Teddy.

544
00:49:02,039 --> 00:49:04,372
<i>I told you, no company.</i>

545
00:49:05,910 --> 00:49:11,508
Thought I might join you, anyway,
as I never like to drink alone.

546
00:49:13,217 --> 00:49:16,915
Well, isn't this a rare honor?

547
00:49:18,055 --> 00:49:20,684
Teddy, you know who this is?

548
00:49:23,060 --> 00:49:24,619
Can't say that I do.

549
00:49:24,895 --> 00:49:27,729
Everything good that has
ever happened in your life,

550
00:49:27,932 --> 00:49:32,302
and everything rotten, this
is the man you have to thank.

551
00:49:35,906 --> 00:49:37,431
How am I doing, Robert?

552
00:49:38,476 --> 00:49:40,638
Any closer to finding
what I'm looking for?

553
00:49:40,811 --> 00:49:43,110
And what is that, exactly?

554
00:49:44,381 --> 00:49:46,247
<i>We're looking for a
man named Wyatt.</i>

555
00:49:46,717 --> 00:49:50,085
Killed a rancher back in
Sweetwater, took his daughter.

556
00:49:52,556 --> 00:49:54,787
That last part
doesn't sound familiar.

557
00:49:55,392 --> 00:49:58,362
Figured your stories could
use a little embellishment.

558
00:49:59,129 --> 00:50:03,260
You know, I always felt this
place was missing a real villain,

559
00:50:03,501 --> 00:50:06,437
hence my humble contribution.

560
00:50:08,272 --> 00:50:12,642
I admit, I lack the imagination to
even conceive of someone like you.

561
00:50:13,744 --> 00:50:16,839
The urgency, however,
doesn't quite fit the character.

562
00:50:17,448 --> 00:50:19,974
It betrays a certain anxiety.

563
00:50:22,720 --> 00:50:27,454
Now, Wyatt, on the other
hand, that's something new.

564
00:50:28,058 --> 00:50:31,256
Is he just another stooge for the
tourists to mount on their wall at home,

565
00:50:31,428 --> 00:50:34,262
or have you finally
made a worthy adversary?

566
00:50:35,733 --> 00:50:40,433
Someone to stop me from
finding the center of the maze.

567
00:50:42,339 --> 00:50:44,808
And what is it you're
hoping to find there?

568
00:50:47,978 --> 00:50:49,970
You know why you exist, Teddy?

569
00:50:51,015 --> 00:50:54,816
The world out there,
the one you'll never see,

570
00:50:55,819 --> 00:50:57,378
is one of plenty.

571
00:50:57,855 --> 00:51:00,950
A fat, soft teat people
cling to their entire life.

572
00:51:01,725 --> 00:51:04,388
Every need taken care of,

573
00:51:04,662 --> 00:51:05,823
except one.

574
00:51:07,164 --> 00:51:08,291
Purpose.

575
00:51:09,400 --> 00:51:10,663
Meaning.

576
00:51:11,535 --> 00:51:13,299
So, they come here.

577
00:51:13,470 --> 00:51:16,065
They can be a little
scared, a little thrilled,

578
00:51:16,240 --> 00:51:18,300
enjoy some sweetly
affirmative bullshit,

579
00:51:18,475 --> 00:51:21,536
and then they take a fucking
picture and they go back home.

580
00:51:22,813 --> 00:51:26,215
But I think there's
a deeper meaning

581
00:51:26,383 --> 00:51:28,477
hiding under all that.

582
00:51:28,819 --> 00:51:33,223
Something that the person
who created it wanted to express.

583
00:51:36,327 --> 00:51:38,125
Something true.

584
00:51:40,130 --> 00:51:42,827
Well, if you're looking
for the moral of the story,

585
00:51:43,033 --> 00:51:44,296
you could quite simply ask.

586
00:51:44,735 --> 00:51:47,034
I'd need a shovel.

587
00:51:47,204 --> 00:51:50,231
The man I'd be asking
died 35 years ago.

588
00:51:50,474 --> 00:51:52,409
Almost took this place with him.

589
00:51:52,643 --> 00:51:56,205
Almost, but not
quite. Thanks to me.

590
00:51:56,847 --> 00:52:00,011
Well, maybe he left
something behind.

591
00:52:02,853 --> 00:52:07,086
I wonder what I would
find if I opened you up.

592
00:52:15,566 --> 00:52:19,901
Even at death's door,
you're still a loyal pet.

593
00:52:27,277 --> 00:52:28,973
Is that why you
came here, Robert?

594
00:52:30,114 --> 00:52:32,083
To try to talk me out of it?

595
00:52:32,483 --> 00:52:34,418
On the contrary.

596
00:52:34,985 --> 00:52:39,389
Far be it from me to get in the
way of a voyage of self-discovery.

597
00:52:50,968 --> 00:52:52,197
Mr. Flood.

598
00:52:52,369 --> 00:52:57,808
We must look back and
smile at perils past, mustn't we?

599
00:53:10,054 --> 00:53:13,889
We should get back on
the road. Time's a-wasting.

600
00:55:07,037 --> 00:55:08,562
<i>Hello, Felix.</i>

601
00:55:12,209 --> 00:55:14,610
It's time you and I had a chat.

602
00:56:30,888 --> 00:56:31,888
English -SDH

